 Nicholas Tooth , 25 , was playing for the Quirindi Lions against the Narrabri Blue Boars in mid-north NSW on Saturday when he collapsed after hitting his head on an opponent 's shoulder during a tackle .
He was treated at the ground before being airlifted to Newcastle 's John Hunter Hospital in a critical condition .
The young man was visiting his home town for the weekend .
Mr Tooth is in the Australian Rugby community .